commentTextItems.html: flicked to fine leg and that's it all over. Heartbreak for Scotland who came so close to a famous upset

commentPostTextItems.html: That's it from us today, good effort from Scotland with ball and bat, especially Haq who bowled a superb spell. A fantastic innings from Chris Gayle snatched victory with the support of Darren Sammy at the end.
Join us for tomorrows game in Belfast, where Scotland must pick themselves up for a game against the Netherlands. Thanks for joining us.
One required off two balls, its game up here surely with Gayle off strike

commentTextItems.html: full ball on middle, flicked through mid wicket. Good fielding in the deep but they pick up three

commentPostTextItems.html: Four needed off three ball- you never know

commentTextItems.html: that could be the game. On a length and he smacked it past cover and to the boundary
full outside off, Sammy plays and misses as he tries to hit to third man
thats a big ball that will keep Gayl off strike, it was full and straight and Gayle could only defend on the front foot

commentPostTextItems.html: Here we go- nine off the last over

commentTextItems.html: full ball, swung away to short fine leg
well bowled, cut out to deep point

milestones.description: This is the highest match aggregate (317) involving teams West Indies & Scotland in ODIs
John Blain has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (22) for SCOT, going past Hamilton

stories.title: West Indies' fragility reappears against brave Scotland
stories.subTitle: Scotland v West Indies, Quad Series, Clontarf
stories.summary: West Indies might have beaten England in the recent one-day series, but an old and unwelcome ghost briefly reappeared today at Clontarf in Dublin as Scotland ran them desperately close in the third match of the Quadrangular series

stories.title: Gayle and Sammy rescue West Indies
stories.subTitle: Scotland v West Indies, Quad Series, Clontarf
stories.seoTitle: Gayle and Sammy rescue West Indies
stories.summary: Chris Gayle kept his cool as West Indies nearly slipped up in dramatic style against Scotland at Clontarf. Chasing a revised 165, they lost six for 38 in seven overs and entered the final three overs needing 29 to win

recentReportStory.title: Gayle and Sammy rescue West Indies
recentReportStory.subTitle: Scotland v West Indies, Quad Series, Clontarf
recentReportStory.seoTitle: Gayle and Sammy rescue West Indies
recentReportStory.summary: Chris Gayle kept his cool as West Indies nearly slipped up in dramatic style against Scotland at Clontarf. Chasing a revised 165, they lost six for 38 in seven overs and entered the final three overs needing 29 to win
